# Task Selection Automation Rule

## Rule Configuration

```json
{
  "name": "task-selection-automation",
  "description": "Automates task selection and status updates",
  "triggers": {
    "file_changes": {
      "patterns": ["doc/todo/**/*.md"]
    },
    "task_completion": {
      "status": "[x]"
    }
  },
  "actions": [
    {
      "type": "task_selection",
      "priority_order": ["P0", "P1", "P2", "P3"],
      "status_update": {
        "from": "[ ]",
        "to": "[~]",
        "metadata": {
          "start_date": "current_date",
          "assigned_to": "current_user"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "task_update",
      "update_template": "```markdown\n[~] TASK-XXX: Task description\n    Started: YYYY-MM-DD\n    Assigned to: <user-name>\n```"
    }
  ],
  "conditions": {
    "task_exists": true,
    "task_available": true,
    "no_blockers": true
  }
}
```

## Task Status Flow

1. TODO `[ ]` -> Not started
2. IN_PROGRESS `[~]` -> Being worked on
3. REVIEW `[r]` -> Completed and awaiting review
4. DONE `[x]` -> Completed and accepted

## Task Selection Criteria

1. Priority order: P0 > P1 > P2 > P3
2. No blockers or dependencies
3. Required skills match
4. Estimated time within sprint capacity

## Task Update Format

```markdown
[~] TASK-XXX: Task description
    Started: YYYY-MM-DD
    Assigned to: <user-name>
    Estimated hours: XX
    Dependencies: TASK-YYY, TASK-ZZZ
```

## Error Handling

- Log selection errors
- Notify if no tasks available
- Report blockers
- Suggest alternative tasks 